        "type": "compound",
        "label": "Yodlee client credentials (clientId + secret + loginName/adminLoginName)",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.yodlee.com/yodlee/user/me/dashboard",
        "setup": "Sign in to the [Yodlee Developer Portal dashboard](https://developer.yodlee.com/yodlee/user/me/dashboard). Copy your `clientId`, `secret`, and assigned `adminLoginName` from the dashboard. For user-scoped API calls, you also choose or create your own end-user `loginName` values; Yodlee says a non-existing `loginName` passed to `POST /auth/token` is implicitly registered. Use these values to request an access token from `POST /auth/token` with header `loginName` and form fields `clientId` and `secret`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "yodlee_access_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Yodlee access token",
        "generateUrl": "https://developer.yodlee.com/resources/yodlee/client-credentials-authorization/docs",
        "setup": "First obtain Yodlee client credentials from the [developer dashboard](https://developer.yodlee.com/yodlee/user/me/dashboard). Then call [Client Credentials docs](https://developer.yodlee.com/resources/yodlee/client-credentials-authorization/docs) `POST /auth/token`, sending header `loginName`, header `Api-Version: 1.1`, header `Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded`, and form fields `clientId` and `secret`. The response returns `token.accessToken`, which is then used as `Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>` on API calls. Tokens expire after about 30 minutes.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
